## Vercel Web Analytics Installation - Implementation Report

### Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for this Next.js App Router project.

### Changes Made

#### 1. Package Installation
- **File**: `package.json`
- **Action**: Added `@vercel/analytics` version 1.6.1 to dependencies
- **Command**: `pnpm i @vercel/analytics`

#### 2. Analytics Component Integration
- **File**: `app/layout.tsx`
- **Changes**:
  - Added import: `import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/next"`
  - Inserted `<Analytics />` component inside the `<body>` tag, after the ThemeProvider closing tag
  - Placement ensures analytics tracking works across the entire application

#### 3. Lock File Update
- **File**: `pnpm-lock.yaml`
- **Action**: Updated with new dependency tree for @vercel/analytics package

### Implementation Details

This is an **App Router** Next.js project (using the `app` directory structure), so the Analytics component was added to the root layout file at `app/layout.tsx`.

The `<Analytics />` component was strategically placed:
- Inside the `<body>` tag for proper rendering
- After the ThemeProvider and all content components
- This ensures the analytics script loads without interfering with the main application rendering

### Verification

✅ **Build Test**: Successfully ran `pnpm run build` - production build completed without errors
✅ **Type Checking**: TypeScript compilation passed with no issues
✅ **Linting**: No new linting errors introduced in modified files (pre-existing errors in other components remain)
✅ **Lock Files**: pnpm-lock.yaml properly updated with new dependencies

### Notes

- The Analytics component will automatically send page view events when deployed to Vercel
- No additional configuration is needed - it works out of the box when deployed
- The component is lightweight and doesn't impact page load performance
- Analytics data will be available in the Vercel dashboard once deployed

### Files Modified
1. `app/layout.tsx` - Added Analytics import and component
2. `package.json` - Added @vercel/analytics dependency
3. `pnpm-lock.yaml` - Updated dependency lock file
